- Mrs. Underwood. - Congresswoman, so good to see you.

347
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:57,350
我也很高兴  请进吧
Wonderful to see you, too. Please, come in.

348
00:26:04,440 --> 00:26:06,650
西莉娅  见到你也很高兴
Celia, so good to see you, too.

349
00:26:07,460 --> 00:26:09,450
很高兴  安德伍德夫人
Always a pleasure, Mrs. Underwood.

350
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:12,970
莉安早先给我打电话  说她来不了了
LeAnn called me a little while ago. Said she couldn't make it.

351
00:26:17,390 --> 00:26:21,160
议员女士  我叫莉安安排这次会议
Congresswoman, I asked LeAnn to have this meeting set up

352
00:26:21,340 --> 00:26:23,910
是因为我有个大胆的提议
because I have a radical proposal,

353
00:26:23,910 --> 00:26:25,600
我想当面跟你提出
and I wanted to make it in person.

354
00:26:27,090 --> 00:26:30,210
道格已经跟我说了
Well, Doug has already filled me in.

355
00:26:30,770 --> 00:26:34,990
我一般不会为任何人背书四年
Usually, I wouldn't endorse anyone four years out,

356
00:26:34,990 --> 00:26:37,860
但这次  我乐意考虑
but in this case, I'm really open to it.

357
00:26:38,090 --> 00:26:42,420
能让民主党人进入州长府邸就好
Anything to put a Democrat into the governor's mansion.

358
00:26:42,420 --> 00:26:43,770
我跟议员女士说
I told the congresswoman that

359
00:26:43,770 --> 00:26:45,690
用上她在达拉斯的政治力量
enlisting her political machinery in Dallas 

360
00:26:45,700 --> 00:26:46,970
是很关键的第一步
is a crucial first step.

361
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:50,020
所以我叫我女儿也一起来了
Which is why I asked my daughter to join us.

362
00:26:50,020 --> 00:26:53,640
到时她已经接替了我的席位  你俩可以密切合作
She'll have my seat by then, and you two will work closely.

363
00:26:54,220 --> 00:26:56,650
我对您十分敬重  安德伍德夫人
I have a great deal of respect for you, Mrs. Underwood.

364
00:26:56,830 --> 00:26:59,060
我认为我们携手可以成就辉煌
I think we can accomplish a lot together.

365
00:26:59,260 --> 00:27:00,570
其实  议员女士
Well, actually, Congresswoman,

366
00:27:00,570 --> 00:27:02,810
我认为如果不先当选公职
I've decided that the governorship is a big leap

367
00:27:02,810 --> 00:27:05,630
直接做州长跨度太大
without holding any elected office first.

368
00:27:05,780 --> 00:27:08,120
你在考虑下一轮竞选参议员吗
Are you thinking Senate next cycle?

369
00:27:08,700 --> 00:27:12,120
不  我在考虑本轮竞选你的选区
No, I'm thinking your district, this cycle.

370
00:27:12,380 --> 00:27:14,660
那样的话  您女儿就得等等
That would mean your daughter holds off,

371
00:27:14,660 --> 00:27:16,970
等我竞选州长时
and then I would throw my full weight behind her

372
00:27:16,980 --> 00:27:18,970
会全力支持她接替我
to replace me when I run for governor.

373
00:27:18,970 --> 00:27:20,610
我已经组织了团队
I've already put together my team.

374
00:27:20,610 --> 00:27:22,710
不  你还是能得到席位的  西莉娅
Oh, no, you would still get the seat, Celia.

375
00:27:23,130 --> 00:27:25,140
我只是求你再等等
I'm just asking you to wait a little longer.

376
00:27:25,380 --> 00:27:27,380
总统认为这个方案最好
And the president thinks this is the best plan.

377
00:27:27,380 --> 00:27:29,150
你怎么没说
Why didn't you tell me this?

378
00:27:29,850 --> 00:27:32,890
-我并不知道  夫人  -他和我私下谈的
- I wasn't aware, ma'am. - Well, he and I spoke privately about it.

379
00:27:32,890 --> 00:27:37,540
西莉娅为了等我退休已经等了十年多
Celia has waited over a decade for me to retire.

380
00:27:37,890 --> 00:27:39,030
该轮到她了
It's her time.

381
00:27:39,030 --> 00:27:40,180
我理解
I understand.

382
00:27:40,180 --> 00:27:43,930
所以等她接过了席位  我希望能给她
And that's why I want to put her in the best position to succeed

383
00:27:43,930 --> 00:27:46,400
-最有利的地位  -你上次踏入
- when she takes office. - When was the last time

384
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:49,380
这个选区是什么时候了
you set foot in this district?

385
00:27:49,460 --> 00:27:51,500
弗兰西斯当选党鞭的时候
When Francis was elected whip.

386
00:27:51,500 --> 00:27:54,230
我们要怎么要求选民支持一个
So, how are we supposed to ask our people to support a woman

387
00:27:54,230 --> 00:27:55,500
根本不了解他们的女人
that doesn't even know them?

388
00:27:56,010 --> 00:27:58,180
不了解他们的生活  他们每日的挣扎
Their lives, their everyday struggles.

389
00:27:58,270 --> 00:27:59,630
投机谋利
Carpetbagger.

390
00:27:59,850 --> 00:28:00,830
还是白人
Who's white.

391
00:28:01,320 --> 00:28:04,490
不仅是种族问题  安德伍德夫人
It goes deeper than race, Mrs. Underwood.

392
00:28:04,930 --> 00:28:08,570
你在海兰帕克长大  从小不缺吃穿
You grew up in Highland Park, never wanted for anything.

393
00:28:09,210 --> 00:28:13,010
你无法体现我们的群体
You just don't reflect our community.

394
00:28:13,010 --> 00:28:14,700
议员女士说得有道理
Congresswoman makes a good point.

395
00:28:18,920 --> 00:28:20,980
我是想要个跳板
What I want is a stepping stone.

396
00:28:21,210 --> 00:28:25,270
而你想联邦资助一家计划生育组织经营的
And what you want is federal funding for a breast cancer center

397
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:26,970
乳腺癌中心
run by Planned Parenthood.

398
00:28:28,810 --> 00:28:31,870
如果共和党控制了国会  这就无法实现
Something that a Republican-controlled Congress will never do.

399
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:34,500
尤其是在退伍军人医院
Especially in a VA hospital.

400
00:28:34,730 --> 00:28:37,910
即便是民主党控制国会时你也遭遇了阻力
You had resistance even when the Democrats controlled the House.

401
00:28:39,130 --> 00:28:42,370
但国会议员  不管是共和党还是民主党
But there's not one congressperson, Republican or Democrat,

402
00:28:42,370 --> 00:28:44,470
都不会拒绝跟第一夫人见面
that would refuse a meeting with the First Lady.

403
00:28:44,690 --> 00:28:46,390
你说得对  安德伍德夫人
You're right, Mrs. Underwood.

404
00:28:48,300 --> 00:28:51,660
我们没能实现我们的一切目标
We haven't accomplished everything we set out to do.

405
00:28:51,770 --> 00:28:55,660
但我的选民一直拥有的
But the one thing my constituents have always had...

406
00:28:56,320 --> 00:29:02,980
是由自己人代表的骄傲
is the pride that they take in being represented by one of their own.

407
00:29:04,330 --> 00:29:08,610
我不想剥夺这份骄傲
I refuse to rob them of that.

408
00:29:09,270 --> 00:29:11,010
多谢您抽时间  议员女士
Thank you for your time, Congresswoman.

409
00:29:11,250 --> 00:29:14,550
我们会重新考虑再联系您  谢谢
We'll reassess our thinking and get back to you. Thank you.

410
00:29:26,150 --> 00:29:28,400
你叫总统别插手
You tell the president to stay out of this.

411
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:30,870
或许您该直接跟他谈
Maybe you should speak to him directly.

412
00:29:31,110 --> 00:29:33,920
如果他肯支持我竞选  我就跟他谈
As soon as he's willing to support this race, I'll talk to him.

413
00:29:34,590 --> 00:29:36,860
您在犯错误  安德伍德夫人
You're making a mistake, Mrs. Underwood.

414
00:29:54,660 --> 00:29:57,540
白宫内部人士透露
A source within the White House tells us this,

415
00:29:57,540 --> 00:29:59,350
第一夫人跟丈夫
that the First Lady traveled to Texas

416
00:29:59,360 --> 00:30:02,170
大吵一架后飞去了德州
after some sort of a major argument with her husband.

417
00:30:00,250 --> 00:30:10,250
{\an8}第一夫人在德州  初选工作还是婚姻分歧

418
00:30:02,230 --> 00:30:04,290
总统称她去达拉斯
Well, the president has claimed that she went to Dallas

419
00:30:04,290 --> 00:30:06,640
是为德州初选打基础
to lay groundwork for the Texas primary.

420
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:10,310
但她三天前抵达后  却不见举办任何
But there's no evidence of any campaign events or fundraisers

421
00:30:10,310 --> 00:30:12,500
竞选活动或筹款活动
since she arrived there three days ago,

422
00:30:12,500 --> 00:30:14,700
也未曾公开露面
and she hasn't appeared publicly.

423
00:30:14,700 --> 00:30:17,380
那么  莫妮卡  得问问你对此事的看法
So, Monica, gotta get your take on this. 

424
00:30:17,610 --> 00:30:19,550
如果真的出现了婚姻不和
Well, if there is marital discord,

425
00:30:19,550 --> 00:30:21,990
安德伍德夫妇肯定不愿承认
the Underwoods certainly wouldn't want to admit it.

426
00:30:21,990 --> 00:30:24,030
她去那边筹备初选
Her being down there for the primary?

427
00:30:24,030 --> 00:30:25,730
拜托  那完全可能是障眼法
Come on, that could be a smokescreen.

428
00:30:25,740 --> 00:30:28,060
-胡安  -格雷琴  我们现实点
- Juan? - Well, come on, Gretchen. Let's be real.

429
00:30:28,070 --> 00:30:29,830
南卡罗莱纳州有蹊跷啊
Something's rotten in the state of Denmark.

430
00:30:29,830 --> 00:30:31,780
这时机简直太糟了
I mean, the timing on this could not be worse.

431
00:30:31,780 --> 00:30:34,910
别忘了  新罕布什尔初选就在明天
Don't forget, the New Hampshire primary is tomorrow.

432
00:30:34,910 --> 00:30:38,200
总统从爱荷华州带出来的好势头
So, whatever momentum the president had coming out of Iowa...

433
00:30:38,690 --> 00:30:40,880
现在都像气球泄气一样流逝了
Just like air going out of a popped balloon.

434
00:30:40,880 --> 00:30:42,880
海瑟·邓巴对此
Well, you know that Heather Dunbar

435
00:30:42,880 --> 00:30:46,270
肯定有话说  我们看看吧
is gonna have something to say about this. Let's take a look.

436
00:30:46,490 --> 00:30:49,150
我不知道此事是真是假
I don't know whether this story is true or not,

437
00:30:46,520 --> 00:30:56,520
{\an8}海瑟·邓巴  针对安德伍德婚姻传言的回应

438
00:30:49,150 --> 00:30:52,160
但如果是  我希望总统和第一夫人
but if it is, I hope that the president and the First Lady

439
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:54,040
能调和矛盾
can work out their differences.

440
00:30:54,290 --> 00:30:57,150
没人希望看到一段婚姻出现问题
No one likes to see a marriage under strain.

441
00:30:58,100 --> 00:31:02,400
个人而言  如果不是我了不起的家人
Personally, I wouldn't be able to carry on my campaign 

442
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:03,590
我也没法竞选...
without the incredible...

443
00:31:03,590 --> 00:31:04,700
知道是哪里走漏的消息吗
Do we know where the leak came from?

444
00:31:04,700 --> 00:31:07,600
我们在找特勤局和员工问话
We're talking to Secret Service and to staff now,

445
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:08,880
但是  先生  暂时还不知道
but no, sir, we don't know yet.

446
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:10,740
我这儿有一堆十磅重的剪报
I'm looking at a ten-pound stack of clippings,

447
00:31:10,740 --> 00:31:12,790
这还只是过去一小时里出来的报道
and that's just what's been written in the past hour.

448
00:31:12,790 --> 00:31:15,160
这是邓巴干的  我知道是她捣的鬼
This is Dunbar. I know she's behind this.

449
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:17,480
先生  我可能有办法了
Sir, I might have a solution.

450
00:31:19,770 --> 00:31:21,440
我们能单独谈谈吗
May we speak privately for a moment?

451
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:23,470
好  赛斯  挂线
Yeah. Seth, hop off the line.

452
00:31:23,470 --> 00:31:25,240
如果我们要改变策略  我觉得...
If we're gonna switch tactics, I think I should--

453
00:31:25,240 --> 00:31:27,730
如果总统打算采取措施我会告诉你的
I'll fill you in if the president wants to move forward.

454
00:31:27,880 --> 00:31:29,480
挂线  赛斯
Hop off, Seth.

455
00:31:29,790 --> 00:31:31,120
在辩论中  我们只记得
During the debates, we all remember,

456
00:31:31,120 --> 00:31:35,110
安德伍德攻击夏普把孩子送去私立学校
Underwood went after Sharp for sending her kids to private...

457
00:31:35,110 --> 00:31:36,130
好吧  说吧
All right, go ahead.

458
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:38,150
克莱尔的母亲
Claire's mother.

459
00:31:38,340 --> 00:31:39,390
她怎么了
What about her?

460
00:31:54,470 --> 00:31:58,200
{\an8}第一夫妇吵架  克莱尔·安德伍德走人

461
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:09,940
你五岁的时候我就告诉你
I told you when you were five years old

462
00:32:09,940 --> 00:32:12,720
进屋一定要跟我打招呼
not to come in this house without saying hello to me.

463
00:32:14,890 --> 00:32:18,020
我到时就去看过你  你当时睡了
I came by when I arrived. You were asleep.

464
00:32:18,410 --> 00:32:20,250
那是两天前了
That was two days ago.

465
00:32:21,350 --> 00:32:23,600
我不知道你是不是想见我  母亲
Well, I wasn't sure you wanted to see me, Mother.

466
00:32:23,600 --> 00:32:24,550
好吧
Well...

467
00:32:24,980 --> 00:32:29,260
既然我们要生活在一个屋檐下
as long as we're living under the same roof

468
00:32:29,340 --> 00:32:33,360
-而且还被新闻车包围  -那个很抱歉
- and besieged by news trucks-- - I apologize for all that.

469
00:32:33,650 --> 00:32:34,980
是真的吗
Is it true?

470
00:32:36,190 --> 00:32:38,250
你是因为这个才过来的吗
Is that why you came down here?

471
00:32:39,550 --> 00:32:41,750
不  我来是因为
No, I came down here because...

472
00:32:45,370 --> 00:32:47,810
那个来访的女人
That woman who visited...

473
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:52,050
-莉安·哈维  -我知道她是谁
- LeAnn Harvey. - Mmm-hmm, I know who she is.

474
00:32:52,050 --> 00:32:56,150
她推销候选人的时候经常打给我
She calls me all the time asking for money when she's...

475
00:32:57,120 --> 00:33:00,330
问我要钱
peddling some candidate.

476
00:33:01,610 --> 00:33:03,770
你是候选人吗
Are you the candidate?

477
00:33:06,040 --> 00:33:08,510
国会  30选区
Congress. 30th District.

478
00:33:08,870 --> 00:33:09,860
这样啊
I see.

479
00:33:12,170 --> 00:33:13,630
你不赞成
You don't approve.

480
00:33:14,270 --> 00:33:17,560
你总是自己做决定
Well, you've always made your choices

481
00:33:17,580 --> 00:33:19,810
不管我怎么想
regardless of what I think.

482
00:33:20,490 --> 00:33:21,980
他怎么想
What does he think?

483
00:33:22,090 --> 00:33:24,440
他跟你谈话了吗  劝我别那么做
Has he spoken to you? To discourage me?

484
00:33:24,840 --> 00:33:28,710
你爸爸葬礼那天之后他就再没跟我说过话
He hasn't spoken to me since the day of your daddy's funeral.

485
00:33:29,630 --> 00:33:31,310
你也一样
Just like you haven't.

486
00:33:31,530 --> 00:33:34,420
你当上第一夫人都不来通电话
Not even a phone call when you became First Lady--

487
00:33:34,420 --> 00:33:36,660
如果你不希望我待在这儿  我可以另做安排
If you don't want me here, I can make other arrangements.

488
00:33:36,660 --> 00:33:38,090
别傻了
Oh, don't be ridiculous.

489
00:33:38,090 --> 00:33:40,920
这房子是我的也是你的
This house is as much yours as it is mine.

490
00:33:41,320 --> 00:33:43,080
我把东西都罩上
I put covers on everything

491
00:33:43,080 --> 00:33:46,640
是因为女仆要清扫我从不进的房间
because the maids were cleaning rooms I never set foot in.

492
00:33:46,640 --> 00:33:48,700
但既然你来了
But now that you're here...

493
00:33:49,140 --> 00:33:50,150
别动了
Just leave them.

494
00:33:51,170 --> 00:33:52,510
我只需要一间卧室
I only need a bedroom.

495
00:33:54,940 --> 00:33:55,900
好吧
Fine.

496
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:59,930
这房子对你来说就是个旅馆
This house is just a hotel to you.

497
00:34:06,390 --> 00:34:09,290
总统今天下午晚些时候会抵达达拉斯
The president will arrive in Dallas later this afternoon.

498
00:34:09,480 --> 00:34:12,540
至于他此行的目的  我目前不能透露
As to the nature of his trip, I can't comment at this time

499
00:34:12,540 --> 00:34:14,830
只能说他打算见第一夫人
other than to say he plans on seeing the First Lady.

500
00:34:15,090 --> 00:34:16,660
-赛斯  -马克
- Seth! - Mark.

501
00:34:16,670 --> 00:34:18,670
他南下似乎让他们出现婚姻问题的说法
His going down there would seem to lend legitimacy

502
00:34:18,680 --> 00:34:21,400
看起来更有依据了  不是吗
to claims that they're having marital issues, wouldn't it?

503
00:34:21,540 --> 00:34:23,470
我们已经否认了那种说法
We've already denied those claims.

504
00:34:23,620 --> 00:34:25,790
-赛斯  -莎拉
- Seth! - Sara.

505
00:34:26,010 --> 00:34:27,660
报道爆出后  总统
Neither the president nor the First Lady

506
00:34:27,660 --> 00:34:30,000
和第一夫人都未曾公开做过回应
have publicly responded since this story broke.

507
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:31,270
他们会回应吗
Can we expect them to?

508
00:34:31,510 --> 00:34:33,570
你所谓的报道  并非报道
What you're calling a story isn't a story.

509
00:34:33,650 --> 00:34:34,760
只是个夺人眼球的标题
It's a flashy headline

510
00:34:34,760 --> 00:34:36,650
帮你们在推特上涨粉
that gives you a bump in Twitter followers.

511
00:34:36,710 --> 00:34:38,280
根本不值得对此做出回应
It doesn't warrant a response,

512
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:41,520
但如果总统或第一夫人决定回应
but if the president or First Lady chooses to make one,

513
00:34:41,900 --> 00:34:43,060
肯定第一个告诉你
you'll be the first to know.

514
00:34:43,060 --> 00:34:44,990
-赛斯  -谢谢大家
- Seth! - Thank you all very much.

515
00:35:32,610 --> 00:35:34,620
-她离开多久了  -没多久
- How long has she been gone? - Not long.

516
00:35:34,880 --> 00:35:36,810
-去了莉安·哈维办公室  -老天
- LeAnn Harvey's office. - Christ.

517
00:35:36,810 --> 00:35:38,100
媒体没跟着她吧
The press didn't follow her, did they?

518
00:35:38,100 --> 00:35:39,680
没有  他们走了条公用设施路
No. They took a utility road out. 

519
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:40,880
没有警察随行
No police escort.

520
00:36:12,700 --> 00:36:15,870
你俩要把问都不问一声就跑来
Are you two gonna make a habit of showing up here

521
00:36:15,870 --> 00:36:18,860
当成习惯吗
without even the courtesy of asking?

522
00:36:18,900 --> 00:36:20,600
我也希望不用来这儿
I wish I didn't have to be here,

523
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:22,780
但你女儿逼得我没办法
but your daughter's made it necessary.

524
00:36:23,020 --> 00:36:24,520
她结婚时
You know, when she got married,

525
00:36:24,520 --> 00:36:27,680
我以为过一两年她肯定会醒悟
I was sure she would wake up in a year or two.

526
00:36:28,350 --> 00:36:31,310
没想到她用了30年
I had no idea it was gonna take her 30.

527
00:36:31,930 --> 00:36:34,710
克莱尔是美国的第一夫人
Claire is the First Lady of the United States,

528
00:36:34,710 --> 00:36:37,750
你还觉得她选错了人
and you still think she made the wrong choice.

529
00:36:37,900 --> 00:36:40,620
变成小报谈资了
Reduced to tabloid gossip?

530
00:36:40,770 --> 00:36:44,170
她跟住在你出身的那个拖车公园有什么区别
She might as well be living in that trailer park you come from.

531
00:36:44,170 --> 00:36:45,580
是个桃子园
Well, it was a peach farm.

532
00:36:45,580 --> 00:36:48,900
但你没说错  我还是白人垃圾
But you're right, I am still white trash.

533
00:36:48,900 --> 00:36:52,730
我只不过恰好是个住在白宫的白人垃圾
I just happen to be white trash that lives in the White House.

534
00:36:53,140 --> 00:36:58,070
就算当上总统  还是那么粗俗
Not even being president could give you any class.

535
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:03,250
我告诉你接下来会怎么样吧  伊丽莎白
Well, let me tell you what's about to happen, Elizabeth.

536
00:37:03,320 --> 00:37:05,590
我不会站在交火的总统
I am not going to put myself in the crossfire

537
00:37:05,590 --> 00:37:07,320
和第一夫人之间
between a president and First Lady.

538
00:37:07,320 --> 00:37:09,040
我来应付弗兰西斯
Oh, I'll handle Francis.

539
00:37:09,190 --> 00:37:10,950
你说他同意的
You said he was on board.

540
00:37:11,350 --> 00:37:13,110
我会让他同意的
And I'll make sure he is.

541
00:37:13,650 --> 00:37:16,200
重点是  你误导了我  安德伍德夫人
The point is you misled me, Mrs. Underwood.

542
00:37:16,340 --> 00:37:19,130
你想要什么  莉安  钱吗
What is it you want, LeAnn? Is it money?

543
00:37:20,580 --> 00:37:23,140
还是想要更多  留下真正的痕迹
Or do you want more, to make a real mark?

544
00:37:23,140 --> 00:37:24,720
我不用选  我可以兼得
I don't have to choose. I can have both.

545
00:37:24,720 --> 00:37:27,620
如果你想青史留名  你就得离开德州
Well, if you wanna make history, you need to get out of Texas.

546
00:37:27,620 --> 00:37:30,010
我拒绝过不少华府的工作
I've turned down plenty of jobs in D.C.

547
00:37:30,010 --> 00:37:32,140
一年应付15位客户
Juggling 15 clients a year.

548
00:37:33,300 --> 00:37:35,550
但我想要你接下来15年的时间
But I want the next 15 years of your life.

549
00:37:36,060 --> 00:37:37,830
德州只是我们的起点
Texas is just where we begin.

550
00:38:03,280 --> 00:38:05,620
看来你到底是没听到
It seems you didn't hear me after all.

551
00:38:05,680 --> 00:38:07,550
我不向威胁低头
I don't respond to threats.

552
00:38:07,550 --> 00:38:09,220
你在跟总统说话
You're speaking to the president.

553
00:38:09,700 --> 00:38:11,410
是的  我认得出他的声音
Yes, I recognize his voice.

554
00:38:11,410 --> 00:38:13,810
请让我单独跟我妻子谈谈
I'd like to talk to my wife alone, please.

555
00:38:13,810 --> 00:38:15,940
她留下  你想跟我说什么就说吧
She stays. Tell me what you need to tell me.

556
00:38:18,420 --> 00:38:19,220
道格
Doug.

557
00:38:32,100 --> 00:38:34,180
她已经病了三年了
She's been sick for three years.

558
00:38:34,500 --> 00:38:36,980
放疗  化疗  都做了
Radiation, chemotherapy, the works.

559
00:38:40,340 --> 00:38:42,290
但你不知道  是吗
But you didn't know, did you?

560
00:38:45,220 --> 00:38:47,370
你不能把我母亲拉到镜头前
You're not dragging my mother in front of the cameras.

561
00:38:47,370 --> 00:38:51,040
只有你一人  你要说你是为此才南下
Just you, and you're going to say that that's why you're down here.

562
00:38:51,200 --> 00:38:53,440
这是家事  弗兰西斯
This is a family matter, Francis.

563
00:38:53,440 --> 00:38:57,100
这事必须做  克莱尔  我们得把传言止住
This has to be done, Claire. We have to kill this story.

564
00:38:57,680 --> 00:38:58,950
他说得对
He's right.

565
00:39:02,900 --> 00:39:05,300
我要知道你不会给我的竞选捣乱
I need to know you won't meddle with my campaign.

566
00:39:07,250 --> 00:39:08,790
国情咨文就在两周之后
The State of the Union is in two weeks.

567
00:39:08,790 --> 00:39:10,880
你到时要来  我就不再阻挠你
You show up for that, then I'll leave you alone.

568
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:12,300
我们赶紧了事吧
Let's get this over with.

569
00:39:35,110 --> 00:39:37,210
克莱尔最初来到达拉斯时
When Claire first came down here to Dallas...

570
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:41,000
我们说是为德州的初选打基础
we said it was to lay the groundwork for the Texas primary.

571
00:39:41,250 --> 00:39:42,920
这也算是事实
And that was partially true.

572
00:39:43,210 --> 00:39:46,460
但我们没说的  是一些本想保密的私事
What we left out was something that we hoped to keep private.

573
00:39:46,910 --> 00:39:49,820
但鉴于这几天来关于我们婚姻状况的
But in light of false stories over the last number of days

574
00:39:49,830 --> 00:39:51,430
漫天谣传
about the state of our marriage,

575
00:39:51,510 --> 00:39:55,480
我们现在认为只能说出这一不幸的消息
we now feel it's important to share this unfortunate news.

576
00:39:55,740 --> 00:39:56,510
克莱尔
Claire.

577
00:39:58,610 --> 00:40:00,020
这三年来
For the past three years,

578
00:40:00,020 --> 00:40:03,260
我母亲一直在与间歇性淋巴癌做抗争
my mother has been suffering from intermittent lymphoma.

579
00:40:04,110 --> 00:40:07,630
起初  她在与病魔的抗争中取得了胜利
Initially, she had some success battling her illness,

580
00:40:07,630 --> 00:40:10,440
但这几个月  疾病复发而且非常严重
but it's come back full force the last several months.

581
00:40:11,340 --> 00:40:13,840
所以  我来这儿陪她
So, I came down here to spend time with her

582
00:40:14,030 --> 00:40:16,160
进行进一步的治疗
while she undergoes further treatment.

583
00:40:16,620 --> 00:40:19,530
看在我母亲尊严和健康的分上
And we ask just for the sake of my mother's dignity...

584
00:40:21,720 --> 00:40:25,340
我们请求大家尊重她的隐私
and well-being that you respect her privacy.

585
00:40:26,590 --> 00:40:27,440
谢谢
Thank you.

586
00:40:30,940 --> 00:40:32,950
我明天将继续我的竞选
I will be resuming my campaign tomorrow

587
00:40:32,950 --> 00:40:35,980
克莱尔  当然了  将留在这里
and Claire will, of course, be staying here.

588
00:40:36,260 --> 00:40:37,680
我还要说
And let me just add...

589
00:40:39,010 --> 00:40:41,790
克莱尔的母亲有这样孝顺的女儿是莫大的福气
Claire's mother is blessed to have such a loving daughter.

590
00:40:42,010 --> 00:40:45,600
我有如此体贴  善良的妻子也是三生有幸
And I am blessed to have such a thoughtful and caring wife.

591
00:40:45,670 --> 00:40:47,060
谢谢大家
Thank you all very much.

592
00:41:12,380 --> 00:41:14,180
平平常常  但也足矣了
Nothing fancy, but it'll do the job.

593
00:41:43,380 --> 00:41:46,130
你正式是约翰·卡莱尔了
You're officially John Carlyle now.

594
00:41:51,490 --> 00:41:55,870
驾照有意弄了个过期的  你得乘大巴上班
Driver's license is expired on purpose. You take the bus to work.

595
00:41:56,640 --> 00:41:59,360
把一切都背下来  地址  生日  社保号
Memorize everything, address, birthday, social.

596
00:41:59,580 --> 00:42:02,070
还有个人经历  也要熟练背下来
There's a personal history in there for you to know by heart, too.

597
00:42:03,540 --> 00:42:05,750
-"飞马租车行"  -对
- "Pegasus Car Rentals"? - Yeah.

598
00:42:06,060 --> 00:42:08,180
你洗租车  明天开始
You wash rentals. It starts tomorrow.

599
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:09,680
保持低调
Keep a low profile.

600
00:42:09,820 --> 00:42:11,110
别表现出异常
Don't be weird about it,

601
00:42:11,180 --> 00:42:12,870
别到处交朋友
don't go out of your way to make friends.

602
00:42:14,870 --> 00:42:16,250
如果...
What if there's...

603
00:42:17,410 --> 00:42:18,560
出什么事了呢
If something's wrong?

604
00:42:19,390 --> 00:42:21,890
固话直接接到我们本地办公室
Landline goes directly to our local office.

605
00:42:21,890 --> 00:42:25,080
出门在外  用旁边那部手机
Away from home, use the cell phone next to it.

606
00:42:26,100 --> 00:42:28,580
还有什么  你有基本的有线台
What else? You have basic cable. 

607
00:42:28,580 --> 00:42:30,250
没有网络  不用说
No Internet, obviously.

608
00:42:31,570 --> 00:42:33,400
百叶窗拉好  门锁好
Keep the blinds drawn and the doors locked.

609
00:42:36,390 --> 00:42:37,240
就这样了
That's it.

610
00:42:43,020 --> 00:42:44,560
本周晚些时候我再来找你
I'll check in with you later this week.

611
00:43:38,380 --> 00:43:42,310
我们不仅在新罕布什尔获胜
Now, we didn't just win a plurality here in New Hampshire.

612
00:43:42,310 --> 00:43:44,230
而且差距悬殊
We won a majority.

613
00:43:46,400 --> 00:43:48,820
知道这意味着什么吗
Now, you know what that tells me?

614
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:51,540
看来等票全数完  邓巴能领先
It's looking like Dunbar's got it by 11 or 12 points

615
00:43:51,540 --> 00:43:53,080
11或12个百分点
by the time everything's counted.

616
00:43:53,080 --> 00:43:54,880
已经报上来几个区了
